# =============================================================================
# paarthurnax/.gitignore
#
# Keeps the paarthurnax/ scaffold safe to push to a public GitHub repo by ignoring
# everything that is instance-specific, secret-bearing, or machine-local.
#
# Rules referenced below:
#   - paarthurnax/CONVENTIONS.md → Workspace & Scratch File Conventions
#   - paarthurnax/CONVENTIONS.md → Connecting to a Remote Agent
#   - paarthurnax/ARCHITECTURE.md → "Model-family folders" → "Keep your customized Modelfile outside paarthurnax/"
#   - paarthurnax/.github/copilot-instructions.md and paarthurnax/CLAUDE.md → "agent should
#     auto-create runtime/ and scratch/ on first use, gitignore them"
# =============================================================================


# --- Mandated by paarthurnax/CONVENTIONS.md (instance-bound, never commit) -----------
# These folders hold real <REMOTE-AI> instance IDs, URLs, tokens, and exported
# artifacts. The scaffold's own briefings promise these are gitignored.
runtime/
scratch/


# --- Per-vendor private config (commit *.example.* siblings instead) ---------
# The README.md inside each of these folders is committable scaffolding.
# The actual live configs below contain secrets and personal preferences.
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/mcp.json
.continue/config.yaml

# (intentionally NOT ignored: .vscode/extensions.json, .vscode/launch.json,
#  .vscode/tasks.json, .cline/.clinerules, .cline/.clineignore,
#  .continue/rules/ — these are project-shared and safe to commit.)


# --- Standard ecosystem ignores ----------------------------------------------
# None of these exist in paarthurnax/ today, but they will the moment any real code
# (e.g. an MCP server stub, build tooling, Python helpers) lands.

# Node.js / npm / pnpm / yarn
node_modules/
.npm/
.pnpm-store/
.yarn/cache/
.yarn/install-state.gz
.yarn/build-state.yml
.pnp.*
npm-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Build outputs
dist/
build/
out/
.cache/
.next/
.nuxt/
.svelte-kit/
.turbo/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# Test / coverage
coverage/
.nyc_output/
*.lcov

# Logs
*.log
logs/


# --- Secrets (never commit, regardless of where they appear) -----------------
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
secrets/
*.local.*


# --- OS / editor noise -------------------------------------------------------
# macOS
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Windows
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# Linux
*~

# Vim / Emacs
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
*~

# JetBrains IDEs (IntelliJ, WebStorm, PyCharm, ...)
.idea/

# Backup / merge leftovers
*.bak
*.orig
*.rej
